included.description:
During my 3 month internship my main focus was Redfin's internal Customer Relationship Management (CRM) tool.
* Conducted 5 user interviews and 5 contextual inquiry observations to understand how real estate agents use internal CRM, coded and synthesized data, and presented recommendations to stakeholders
* Conducted Research study for customer-facing feature using usertesting.com and presented findings and recommendations to stakeholders
* Conducted 3 user interviews by phone, presented findings and recommendations to product manager and UX designer
* Created and promoted repository of known UX issues, drove changes by advising stakeholders
* Wrote UX research manual for engineers and product managers
included.title: User Research Intern

included.title: Digital Analyst

included.summary: I am a graduate student at the University of Michigan's School of Information, specializing in Human Computer Interaction. I am passionate about creating User Experiences that bring joy to the user and that make a positive difference. My training in computer science allows me to quickly grasp new technologies and to understand what's going on under the hood. As a digital analyst, I use quantitative data to inform my research and like to visualize data to make it more meaningful. My experience as a technical writer helps me to craft engaging stories and to listen to the user. As a designer, I combine my analytical acumen with my my empathy for the end user and I am not afraid to iterate in order to hone in on the perfect solution.
included.headline: UX Researcher
